The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 21 February is 222,461 (25,639.9 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 16 February, there were 6,624 new confirmed cases (763.5 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 09 February, there were 8,555 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 23% (1,931 fewer cases).
